msgid ""
"Use ``@`` (position-at) and ``%`` (tangent-at) to construct geometry "
"relative to existing geometry. Typical uses include starting a new edge at "
"an exact point on another edge, or aligning a new edge direction to a "
"sampled tangent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:93
msgid ":class:`~operations_generic.mirror`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:94
msgid ""
"Enforces symmetry by reflecting geometry about a plane, producing mirrored "
"entities with exact geometric correspondence to the source."
msgstr ""

