msgid "Multiple Solutions and Qualification"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:140
msgid ""
"Tangency construction is typically multi-solution. A single problem "
"statement can produce several valid geometric branches depending on where "
"the solution lies relative to the reference entities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:144
msgid ""
"For example, a circle of fixed radius tangent to two secant circles can "
"produce up to eight valid solutions as shown below. This is expected "
"behavior, not an error."
