#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:291
msgid "Coincident"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:302
msgid ""
"The second line starts at ``l1 @ 1`` (the end of ``l1``), creating an exact "
"coincident relationship without a separate constraint object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:306
msgid "Tangent"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:317
msgid ""
"The arc starts at the line endpoint and uses ``l1 % 1`` as its initial "
"tangent direction. This is a direct tangent construction: continuity is "
"encoded in the creation call."
