#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:405
msgid "Tangency qualifiers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:407
msgid "Tangency qualifiers come from OCCT and are exposed as ``Tangency``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:409
msgid "``Tangency.UNQUALIFIED``: no side preference (OCCT ``Unqualified``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:411
msgid ""
"``Tangency.OUTSIDE``: tangent on the exterior side of the target (OCCT "
"``Outside``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:413
msgid ""
"``Tangency.ENCLOSING``: solution encloses/includes the target (OCCT "
"``Enclosing``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:415
msgid ""
"``Tangency.ENCLOSED``: solution is enclosed/included by the target (OCCT "
"``Enclosed``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:418
msgid ""
"These semantics are most visible for curve-vs-curve constraints (for example"
" circle to circle, line to circle). In many practical cases, ``UNQUALIFIED``"
" is a good default followed by filtering via ``selector``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:443
msgid ""
"In the \"egg-plant\" example, ``Tangency.OUTSIDE`` and "
"``Tangency.ENCLOSING`` reduce the candidate branches to the intended outer "
"profile. The selector on ``l2`` then resolves the remaining ambiguity "
"deterministically by choosing the highest branch in ``Y``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:447
msgid "OCCT defines exterior/interior using orientation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:449
msgid ""
"Circle: exterior is on the right side when traversing by its orientation "
"(interior/material is on the left side)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:451
msgid ""
"Line/open curve: interior is the left side with respect to traversal "
"direction, exterior is the opposite side."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:454
msgid ""
"Because of this, changing an input edge direction can change which branches "
"satisfy ``OUTSIDE``/``ENCLOSING``/``ENCLOSED``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:457
msgid ""
"If qualifier behavior appears inverted, inspect input edge orientation "
"first."
msgstr ""

