"cad-viewer>`_ viewer is very handy as it allows the image to be used as a "
"visual guide when creating the sketch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:702
msgid "Within the following code the following conventions are used:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:704
msgid "construction geometry is labeled with a ``c_...``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:705
msgid "arcs are labeled with a ``a<radius>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:706
msgid "lines and polylines are labeled with a ``l...``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:708
msgid ""
"The code starts immediately above the origin (arbitrarily set to the origin "
"of the circle) where a straight line 10° off the x-axis originates. The code"
" then walks around the diagram clockwise creating the perimeter of the "
"object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:750
msgid "Implementation notes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:752
msgid ""
"Build in traversal order around the perimeter. This keeps references local "
"and makes later edits easier because each segment depends on nearby "
"geometry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:754
msgid ""
"Keep helper entities private (``mode=Mode.PRIVATE``) so only final profile "
"edges contribute to the resulting face."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:756
msgid ""
"Use named construction geometry (``c_...``) for intersections and arc "
"centers; this improves readability and debugability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:758
msgid ""
"Use constrained constructors only where they add value (for example "
":class:`~objects_curve.ConstrainedArcs`), and use direct primitives "
"elsewhere."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:760
msgid ""
"Create a :class:`~topology.Face` (``make_face`` then center-hole "
"subtraction) only after the perimeter is fully defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:764
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:766
msgid "Too many results: add qualifiers and a stricter ``selector``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:768
msgid ""
"No results: relax qualifier (start with ``UNQUALIFIED``) and verify geometry"
" is coplanar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:770
msgid ""
"Unstable branch selection: avoid index-only selection when topology changes;"
" prefer geometric sorting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_constraints.rst:772
msgid ""
"Builder mode unexpectedly adds many edges: provide ``selector`` explicitly "
"in the constructor call."
msgstr ""
